          <p><strong>Install Yoast Free if</strong> you run a WordPress site and want the basics covered — sitemaps, meta tags, focus-keyword scoring, schema. <strong>Buy Yoast Premium if</strong> you publish weekly and want internal linking suggestions + multiple keywords per post. <strong>Skip Yoast Premium if</strong> you publish monthly or use RankMath happily. None of it writes content. If you want done-for-you SEO articles published to WordPress, theStacc handles 30 articles per month from $99/mo.</p>
