        <h2 id="verdict">Is Yoast SEO worth it in 2026? Final verdict</h2>
        <p><strong>For every WordPress site: install something.</strong> Yoast Free or RankMath Free covers 80% of on-page SEO. Not having an SEO plugin in 2026 is leaving rankings on the table.</p>

        <p><strong>For established WordPress sites publishing weekly: Yoast Premium is worth it.</strong> Internal linking suggestions and multiple focus keywords genuinely save time. $99/yr is rounding error in a real content budget.</p>

        <p><strong>For local service businesses: Local add-on is overpriced.</strong> The $79/yr Local add-on adds Local Business schema and store-locator features but does not post to GBP. Pair Yoast with a platform that handles GBP, or use theStacc Bundle which includes both.</p>

        <p><strong>For new sites: try RankMath Free first.</strong> It is genuinely more generous on the free tier. If the UX bothers you, switch to Yoast — both plugins import each other's settings.</p>

